title: Guinea president re-elected in first round of voting: Provisional results
text:
CONAKRY: Guinean leader Alpha Conde was re-elected to a second term in the first round of the country's disputed presidential polls, according to provisional results released on Friday.
Results so far from the electoral commission, corresponding to 90 per cent of registered voters, showed Conde winning an outright majority with around 2.2 million votes. Turnout in the election, which the opposition denounced as a "masquerade", was given at around 66 per cent, well below an initial estimate of 75 per cent.
